# PalDefender (formerly PalGuard) - Latest Command Reference

Extracted from commands.txt, showing only the latest syntax as of v1.4.3 (June 27, 2025).

Note: The tool was renamed from "PalGuard" to "PalDefender" in v1.1.6.2495 due to DMCA. UserIDs now require platform prefix: steam_XXXXXXX or gdk_XXXXXXX.


## Teleportation

/tp <X> <Y> [Z]  -  Teleport yourself to map coordinates (Z optional)
/tp <UserId>  -  Teleport yourself to a player
/tp home  -  Teleport to your nearest BaseCamp
/tp oilrig  -  Teleport to nearest OilRig
/tp oilrig:Lv30  -  Teleport to specific OilRig (Lv30, Lv55, Lv60)
/tp <UserID1> <UserID2>  -  Teleport user 1 to user 2 (RCON supported)
/tp <UserID> <X> <Y> <Z>  -  Teleport a player to coordinates
/tp <UserID> home  -  Teleport a player to their closest base
/tp <UserID> oilrig  -  Teleport a player to closest oilrig


## Player Management

/kick <UserId>  -  Kick a player
/ban <UserId>  -  Ban a player (formerly /banid)
/ipban <UserId>  -  IP ban a player (formerly /ipbanid)
/banip <IP>  -  Ban a specific IP (formerly /ipban_ip)
/unbanip <IP>  -  Remove an IP from ban list (formerly /unban_ip)
/setadmin <UserId>  -  Temporarily grant/revoke admin from a player
/getip <UserId>  -  Get the IP of an online player
/renameplayer <UserID> <NewName>  -  Rename an online player
/spectate  -  Toggle spectate mode (shortcut: \ key, admin only)
/godmode [on/off]  -  Toggle invulnerability, one-shot (if allowAdminCheats), no food/durability loss
/adminlogin  -  Alias for /adminpassword
/adminlogout  -  Log out of admin mode


## Item Commands

/give <UserId> <ItemID> <Amount>  -  Give a player items
/giveme <ItemID> <Amount>  -  Give yourself items
/giveitems ...  -  Give multiple items (added v1.1199)
/delitem <UserId> <ItemID> <Amount>  -  Remove items from player inventory. Amount=0 shows count without removing
/delitems ...  -  Delete multiple items (added v1.1199)
/give_relic <UserId> <Amount>  -  Give Lifmunk Effigies
/giveme_relic [Count]  -  Give yourself Lifmunk Effigies (negative to subtract)
/clearinv <UserID> [Container:Array]  -  Clear player inventory. Containers: items, keyitems, armor, weapons, food, dropslot, or all


## Experience & Stats

/give_exp <UserId> <Amount>  -  Give experience to a player (gives in small radius around player)
/givestats <UserId> <numStats>  -  Give stat points to a player (default 0 = displays unused points)
/givemestats <numStats>  -  Give yourself stat points


## Technology

/givetech <UserId> [Count]  -  Give Technology Points (negative to subtract)
/givemetech [Count]  -  Give yourself Technology Points (negative to subtract)
/givebosstech <UserId> [Count]  -  Give Ancient Technology Points (negative to subtract)
/givemebosstech [Count]  -  Give yourself Ancient Technology Points (negative to subtract)
/learntech <UserID> <TechID>  -  Let a player learn a technology (TechID can be "all")
/unlearntech <UserID> <TechID>  -  Let a player forget a technology (TechID can be "all")
/gettechids  -  List all available tech IDs (RCON gets JSON output)


## Pal Commands

/givepal <UserId> <PalID> [Level]  -  Give a Pal (Level defaults to 1, random stats/passives)
/givemepal <PalID> [Level]  -  Give yourself a Pal (Level defaults to 1)
/givepal_j <UserId> <PalTemplate>  -  Give Pal from PalTemplate JSON (supports SkinId)
/givemepal_j <PalTemplate>  -  Give yourself a Pal from PalTemplate JSON
/spawnpal <PalID> [X] [Y] [Z] [Level=1]  -  Spawn a wild Pal (RCON requires coordinates)
/spawnpal_j <PalTemplate> [X] [Y] [Z]  -  Spawn a wild Pal from PalTemplate (RCON requires coordinates)
/deletepals ...  -  Delete pals (added v1.1199)
/exportpals [UserId]  -  Export equipped Pals to PalDefender/Pals/Templates/ folder
/removedroppedpals  -  Remove Pals dropped on the ground
/jetragon  -  Give yourself an admin Jetragon (max level, fast)
/catwaifu  -  Give yourself an admin Cat Waifu (buffs character stats, max level)


## Egg Commands

/giveegg <UserID> <EggID> <PalID> [Level=1]  -  Give a player an egg with specific Pal inside
/givemeegg <EggID> <PalID> [Level=1]  -  Give yourself an egg
/giveegg_j <UserID> <EggID> <PalTemplate> [Level=1]  -  Give egg using PalTemplate
/givemeegg_j <EggID> <PalTemplate> [Level=1]  -  Give yourself egg using PalTemplate


## Base & Guild Commands

/getnearestbase  -  Shows guild name and UID of nearest base (uses map coords)
/gotonearestbase  -  Teleport to nearest base (uses map coords)
/killnearestbase  -  Destroy nearest base (uses map coords, use with caution)
/setguildleader ...  -  Set guild leader (added v1.1199)
/exportguilds  -  Export guild data (includes MapPosition, WorldPosition, LastOnlineTicks, LastOnlineUnix, GuildChest, Pal Labor Research Lab, Expeditions)


## OilRig Management

/resetoilrig <oilrig>  -  Reset OilRig boxes/enemies. Options: lv30, lv55, lv60, all


## Server & Utility

/pgbroadcast <message>  -  Broadcast message (supports spaces, unlike vanilla)
/alert <message>  -  Show big red important text (like meteor text). Use \n for multi-lines
/settime <hour>  -  Set time of day (values: 0-23, day, night)
/reloadcfg  -  Reload PalDefender config and refreshes Palworld banlist
/getrconcmds  -  Get all RCON available commands and argument counts
/getskinids  -  List all available Pal Skin IDs (RCON gets JSON output, formerly /skins)


## Whitelist Commands

/whitelist_add <UserId>  -  Add to whitelist (supports IP with wildcards: 75.115.*.*)
/whitelist_remove <UserId>  -  Remove from whitelist
/whitelist_get  -  Get full list of whitelisted players
